<paragraph id="663E369ADD165A3FFF7AFCE3CD92CD2C" blockId="20.[227,436,844,870]" box="[227,436,844,870]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<heading id="3D7681F6DD165A3FFF7AFCE3CD92CD2C" bold="true" box="[227,436,844,870]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="3">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFF7AFCE3CD92CD2C" bold="true" box="[227,436,844,870]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Shell description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD165A3FFF7AFCD4CE14CA6B" blockId="20.[226,1437,890,1057]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Large (estimated SL: 
<quantity id="A1799B7FDD165A3FFE78FCD4CE7ACDDF" box="[481,604,891,917]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7269999999999999" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="172.7">172.7 mm</quantity>
), elongate, sturdy shell. Spire whorl outline conical. Early spire whorls conical, later spire whorls conical, with slightly convex outline. Shoulder rounded, with maximum diameter just below shoulder. Suture slightly impressed. Subsutural flexure very shallow, very weakly curved, nearly symmetrical (
<figureCitation id="FEBA2A1FDD165A3FFDA9FC4BCEBDCDB4" box="[560,667,996,1022]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="61.[227,270,1647,1673]" captionTargetBox="[227,1437,912,1604]" captionTargetId="figure-374@61.[227,1437,912,1604]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="Fig. 40. Examples of subsutural flexures. A. Conus (Lautoconus) eschewegi Pereira da Costa, 1866 (MNHN.F.A82976). B. Conus (Lautoconus) ictini sp. nov. (AMPG(IV) 3719). C. Conus (Lautoconus) sp. 1 (MNHN.F.A82982). D. Conus (Lautoconus) sp. 2 (AMPG(IV) 3756). E. Conus (Lautoconus) sp. 3 (MNHN.F.A83012). F. Conus (Lautoconus) cf. baldichieri Borson, 1820 (MNHN.F.A83013). G. Conus (Lautoconus) lauriatragei sp. nov. (MNHN.F.A83014). H. Conus (Lautoconus) damianakisi sp. nov. (AMPG(IV) 3802). I. Conus (Lautoconus) sp. 4 (MNHN.F.A83015). J. Conus (Lautoconus) sp. 5 (AMPG(IV) 3861). K. Conus (Stephanoconus) cf. taurinensis Bellardi &amp; Michelotti, 1841 (AMPG(IV) 3808). L. Conus (Stephanoconus) moissettei sp. nov. (MNHN.F.A83071). M. Conus davolii sp. nov. (MNHN.F.A83091). N. Conus fuscocingulatus Hörnes, 1851 (AMPG(IV) 3858). O. Conus (Plagioconus) elatus Michelotti, 1847 (AMPG(IV) 3862). P. Conus (Plagioconus) sp. (AMPG(IV) 3890). Q. Conus (Plagioconus) sp. (AMPG(IV) 3898). R. Conus (Plagioconus) aquensis d’Orbigny, 1852 (AMPG(IV) 3907). Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484351" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484351/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 40E</figureCitation>
). Last whorl elongated, straight. Aperture straight. Apertural canal short, wide, fasciole twisted.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD165A3FFF7AFBE6CE3ECA29" blockId="20.[227,536,1097,1123]" box="[227,536,1097,1123]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<heading id="3D7681F6DD165A3FFF7AFBE6CE3ECA29" bold="true" box="[227,536,1097,1123]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="3">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFF7AFBE6CE3ECA29" bold="true" box="[227,536,1097,1123]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Colour pattern variation</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD165A3FFF7AFBD8CFF1CB2E" blockId="20.[227,1437,1143,1381]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Three levels of colouration are present in this species. The first one consists of two fluorescent bands, which are on the middle and anterior parts of the shell. The second one is a pattern of spirally arranged alterations of non-fluorescent and fluorescent dots. The third level is displayed between the spiral alterations of dots. It consists of a series of fluorescent, arrow-like blotches-tents, pointing in the opposite direction of the shell growth, alternated by non-fluorescent areas. The non-fluorescent areas might have one or two dots between the fluorescent arrows. Along with the second level of fluorescent dots, irregular fluorescent flammulae appear on the spire whorls.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2E9B6511DD165A3FFF7AFA23CF41C644" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="663E369ADD165A3FFF7AFA23CD73CBEC" blockId="20.[227,341,1420,1446]" box="[227,341,1420,1446]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<heading id="3D7681F6DD165A3FFF7AFA23CD73CBEC" bold="true" box="[227,341,1420,1446]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="3">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFF7AFA23CD73CBEC" bold="true" box="[227,341,1420,1446]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD165A3FFF7AFA15CD79C9D4" blockId="20.[226,1437,1466,1950]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
The colour pattern of the species is unique in the studied material.The relatively rounded spire whorls and the lack of tubercles on early spire whorls allow us to categorize it as an elongated 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD165A3FFB3FFA71C9B1CBB2" authority="" authorityName="Monterosato" authorityYear="1923" box="[1190,1431,1502,1528]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Lautoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFB3FFA71C8D7CBB2" box="[1190,1265,1502,1528]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFA9BFA70C9ADCBB2" box="[1282,1419,1503,1528]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Lautoconus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD165A3FFF7AF9AECD53C851" author="Caze B." box="[227,373,1537,1563]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="ref28783" refString="Caze B. 2010. Interet systematique de l'etude des motifs colores residuels chez les mollusques du Cenozoique d'Europe. PhD Thesis, MNHN, Paris." type="book" year="2010">Caze (2010)</bibRefCitation>
identified this specimen (MNHN.F. 
<accessionNumber id="79D2AB79DD165A3FFCB8F9AECFA5C851" box="[801,899,1537,1563]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/A30844" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">A30844</accessionNumber>
) (
<figureCitation id="FEBA2A1FDD165A3FFC07F9AECFD3C851" box="[926,1013,1537,1563]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="19.[227,270,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[227,1437,474,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-110@19.[227,1437,474,1895]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Fig. 10. Conus (Lautoconus) sp. 3 from the Tortonian of Crete, (Greece) on apertural, abapertural and apical views, under natural (A1, A3, A5, A6) and UV light. A. Specimen MNHN.F.A83012, Crete. B. Specimen MNHN.F.A30844, Voleones: figured of Caze (2010: fig. 33f) showing the colour pattern of this very large specimen under UV light. Scale bars: A1–A4, B1–B2 = 1 cm; A5 = 500 μm; A6 = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484287" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484287/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) as 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD165A3FFBB0F9AECD8AC875" authority="d'Orbigny, 1852" authorityName="d'Orbigny" authorityYear="1852" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="clavatulus" subGenus="Chelyconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFBB0F9AEC852C851" box="[1065,1140,1537,1563]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFB11F9AEC937C851" box="[1160,1297,1537,1563]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Chelyconus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFABDF9AEC9BBC851" box="[1316,1437,1537,1563]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">clavatulus</emphasis>
d’Orbigny, 1852
</taxonomicName>
, originally described from the early Miocene of Saubrigues (
<collectingCountry id="1E96760ADD165A3FFB3BF98BC8DFC874" box="[1186,1273,1572,1598]" name="France" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">France</collectingCountry>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD165A3FFA88F98BC9BEC874" author="Hall C. A. Jr." box="[1297,1432,1572,1598]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="111 - 171" refId="ref29646" refString="Hall C. A. Jr. 1966. Middle Miocene Conus (Class Gastropoda) from Piedmont, Northern Italy. Bollettino della Societa Paleontologica Italiana 3 (2): 111 - 171." type="journal article" year="1966">Hall (1966</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 23 figs 23–24) illustrated the type material (a 
<typeStatus id="B93A8838DD165A3FFCB9F9E7CF5DC828" box="[800,891,1608,1634]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">syntype</typeStatus>
from the early Miocene of “Dax-Saubrigues”, 
<collectingRegion id="A445F878DD165A3FFF7AF9C5CD7FC8CF" box="[227,345,1642,1669]" country="France" name="Aquitaine" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Aquitaine</collectingRegion>
) of 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD165A3FFE10F9C4CE72C8CE" authorityName="d'Orbigny" authorityYear="1852" box="[393,596,1642,1669]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="clavatulus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFE10F9C4CE72C8CE" box="[393,596,1642,1669]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Conus clavatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the collection of Grateloup. The shell of this specimen resembles 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD165A3FFF7AF921CDF7C8E2" authority="" authorityName="Monterosato" authorityYear="1923" box="[227,465,1678,1704]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Lautoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFF7AF921CD08C8E2" box="[227,302,1678,1704]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFEA7F920CDE1C8E2" box="[318,455,1679,1704]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Lautoconus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
sp. 3. 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD165A3FFD84F921CFE2C8E3" authority="d'Orbigny, 1852" authorityName="d'Orbigny" authorityYear="1852" box="[541,964,1678,1705]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="subclavatus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFD84F921CEDCC8E2" box="[541,762,1678,1704]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Conus subclavatus</emphasis>
d’Orbigny, 1852
</taxonomicName>
, another species of the early Miocene of the 
<collectingRegion id="A445F878DD165A3FFE94F91ECDA7C881" box="[269,385,1713,1739]" country="France" name="Aquitaine" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Aquitaine</collectingRegion>
Basin, is known from a 
<typeStatus id="B93A8838DD165A3FFD3DF91ECED9C881" box="[676,767,1713,1739]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">syntype</typeStatus>
(MNHN.F. 
<accessionNumber id="79D2AB79DD165A3FFC11F91ECFCEC886" box="[904,1000,1713,1740]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/A13055" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">A13055</accessionNumber>
) of the d’Orbigny’s collection and is rather similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD165A3FFE3FF97ACE56C8A4" authorityName="d'Orbigny" authorityYear="1852" box="[422,624,1748,1775]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="clavatulus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFE3FF97ACE56C8A4" box="[422,624,1748,1775]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Conus clavatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Since the patterns of both species remain unknown, we refrain from attributing the Cretan specimens to one of these species. Additionally, 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFB89F957C80DC958" box="[1040,1067,1784,1810]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C.</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD165A3FFBA5F957C8E3C95B" authorityName="Monterosato" authorityYear="1923" box="[1084,1221,1784,1809]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Lautoconus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFBA5F957C8E3C95B" box="[1084,1221,1784,1809]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Lautoconus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) sp. 3 differs from the figured specimens of 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD165A3FFD8BF8B4CF11C97F" author="Kovacs Z. &amp; Vician Z." box="[530,823,1818,1845]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="53 - 100" refId="ref30426" refString="Kovacs Z. &amp; Vician Z. 2013. Badenian (Middle Miocene) Conoidean (Neogastropoda) fauna from Letkes (N Hungary). Fragmenta Palaeontologica Hungarica 30: 53 - 100." type="journal article" year="2013">Kovács &amp; Vicián (2013)</bibRefCitation>
from the Langhian of 
<collectingCountry id="1E96760ADD165A3FFBD2F8B4C895C97F" box="[1099,1203,1819,1845]" name="Hungary" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Hungary</collectingCountry>
, named 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD165A3FFA81F8B4CE1AC913" authority="(d'Orbigny, 1852)" baseAuthorityName="d'Orbigny" baseAuthorityYear="1852" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Varioconus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="clavatulus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFA81F8B4CD7AC912" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Varioconus clavatulus</emphasis>
(d’Orbigny, 1852)
</taxonomicName>
, in the higher spire and the more angulated shoulder. Finally, this species is not 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD165A3FFEB3F8CECF75C931" authority="Brocchi, 1814" authorityName="Brocchi" authorityYear="1814" baseAuthorityName="Brocchi" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[298,851,1889,1915]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ponderosus" subGenus="Lautoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFEB3F8CECD53C931" box="[298,373,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFE1FF8CDCE29C931" box="[390,527,1890,1915]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Lautoconus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD165A3FFDB9F8CECE80C931" box="[544,678,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">ponderosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD165A3FFD34F8CECF75C931" author="Brocchi G." box="[685,851,1889,1915]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="ref28745" refString="Brocchi G. 1814. Conchiologia fossile subapennina, con osservazioni geologiche sugli Apennini e sul suolo adiacente. Stamperia reale, Milano. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11569" type="book" year="1814">Brocchi, 1814</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as it has a slightly higher spire and more elongate last whorl.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD165A3FFF7AF86ACDFCC9AA" blockId="20.[227,474,1989,2016]" box="[227,474,1989,2016]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
